news.title: EPFO to gather data on construction workers in Goa to promote welfare schemes
news.para: EPFO regional office in Goa has been asked to get information on construction workers from the Goa Real Estate Regulatory Authority (RERA), the Building and other Construction Workers’ Welfare Board and Credai.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body allowed commercial activity in residential areas: Punjab governor told
news.para: ​The members claimed that there was gross violation of statutory provisions of the Master Plan of Ludhiana by municipal corporation (MC) officials by converting residential roads into commercial roads by merely giving nod to the resolution in the MC General House.

news.title: Changes in building by-laws in Rajasthan dampen developers' spirit
news.para: As per new norms, a developer can construct a building up to 12.5 metre high (including ground floor and three storeys) on plots below or up to 225 square metres situated on 60-feet roads.

news.title: Company managing construction & demolition plant told to clear waste across Gurugram
news.para: Officials said the scope of work of the firm authorised it to lift waste within a 15km radius of their plant and process it. It has, however, been asked to expand its work across the city.

news.title: Kolkata: HIDCO to e-auction 7.4 acre land in Tollygunge on Jan 11
news.para: The authorities have fixed a starting bid price of Rs 125 crore, at Rs 17 crore for per acre. The e-auction has been scheduled on on January 11.

news.title: Hyderabad: High court pulls up HMDA for failing to protect 750-acre land
news.para: ​Ramky questioned the decision of the sub-registrar of Maheshwaram in refusing to allow registration of flats, plots and villas on land parcel.

news.title: Collectors to shut down illegal stone quarries: Maharashtra revenue minister
news.para: The minister said the collectors have been told to collate data of stone quarries, as well as measure them, and send these details before the sand mining policy is finalised.

news.title: Telangana: Rangareddy, Medchal contribute 40% of registration & stamp wing's revenue
news.para: Of all the 33 districts in Telangana, Rangareddy and Medchal-Malkajgiri districts, which are considered 'cash cows' by the state government of Telangana, contributed nearly 40% of the revenue, about 4,000 crore of 9,400 crore.

news.title: Centrum Housing acquires home loan book of National Trust Housing for Rs 112 crore
news.para: ​Centrum Housing has entered into a binding agreement to acquire the housing finance business of National Trust Housing Finance, the Centrum group said in a statement, without disclosing the value of the transaction.

news.title: Home buyers stage protest outside Raheja Developers' office over delayed deliveries
news.para: ​Home buyers were demanding that the builder should either hand over the houses or refund the money. They alleged that buyers of the Raheja Revanta Project at Sector 78 are awaiting for the last five years for the delivery of their homes.

news.title: China Evergrande Group expects to hit 2022 property delivery target
news.para: The company aims to deliver 300,000 units this year, after delivering 256,000 between January and November, it said in a statement, citing Hui's comments in the meeting.

news.title: Rajasthan govt made changes in building by-laws under influence of realtors: Officials
news.para: On Tuesday government had made a few changes in the building bylaws of the state. Effectively, the government has decided not to allow big buildings on smaller plots measuring up to 750 sq.m.

news.title: Government amends rules to allow extraction of sand in Goa
news.para: In addition, the applicant should either have been born and had his birth registered in Goa, or have any parent or grandparent born in Goa, to apply to the government for permission.

news.title: HC quashes Nagpur Improvement Trust land allotment to private society
news.para: Petitioner Malvi Suvarnakar Sanstha through Adv Anand Parchure, had approached the court challenging the NIT's decision to allot plot no. 8 (khasra no.538) in its layout in Manewada.

news.title: Three lakh people to pay higher property tax in Chennai
news.para: ​Officials said several buildings over the years have done reconstruction or remodelling that have not yet been assessed. This drive with the help of GIS mapping will help to achieve that.
